<subSubSection id="C379979F163D367FAE76FD29DDB83004" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BDCC414163D367FAE76FD29DDB83004" blockId="6.[869,1493,666,787]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="B9171806163D367FAE76FD29DDE831A4" bold="true" box="[869,1005,666,691]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Etymology:</emphasis>
The epithet 
<taxonomicName id="4C63BF97163D367FA96DFD29DAFD31A4" authorityName="Biffi &amp; Geiser" authorityYear="2020" box="[1150,1272,666,691]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Peltariosilis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diversicollis">
<emphasis id="B9171806163D367FA96DFD29DAFD31A4" box="[1150,1272,666,691]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">diversicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is formed from the Latin words 
<emphasis id="B9171806163D367FAEFCFD09DA4331C4" box="[1007,1094,698,723]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">diversus</emphasis>
(different) + 
<emphasis id="B9171806163D367FA9CBFD09DB2431C4" box="[1240,1313,698,723]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">collum</emphasis>
(“neck”, prothorax), referring to the distinct shape of prothorax in this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
